{"name": "write", "args": {"path": "workspace/prophecy/chapter-001.md", "content": "# Chapter 1: The Discovery

Mira had been tracking the Serpent Constellation for three nights when she found the ravine. The ground gave way beneath her feet and she tumbled into darkness, landing on a bed of moss. She lit her lantern and gasped. The walls were covered in carvings — spiraling symbols that told a story. She traced them with her finger and read aloud: When the sky weeps fire, the chosen must choose: sacrifice or ruin. Her hands trembled. This was the Starfall Prophecy, lost for centuries. She had to tell someone.
"}}

{"name": "write", "args": {"path": "workspace/prophecy/chapter-002.md", "content": "# Chapter 2: The Interpretation

Mira spread the rubbings across her study floor. The symbols formed a map of the night sky, with one star marked in red. A hooded figure appeared at her door. "I am Orin, guardian of the temple. You should not have read the carvings." Mira did not flinch. "The prophecy says a star will fall in three nights. The kingdom will burn unless a sacrifice is made." Orin was silent for a long moment. "There is more. The sacrifice must be willing." Mira looked at the map. "Then I will find another way. There must be."
"}}

{"name": "write", "args": {"path": "workspace/prophecy/chapter-003.md", "content": "# Chapter 3: The Choice

The third night arrived. The sky burned crimson as the star grew closer. Mira stood in the temple with Orin. The altar pulsed with light. "There is one detail you missed in the carvings," Mira said. She pointed to a symbol. "The word is not sacrifice. It is transformation." Orin stared. "You would become something else." Mira stepped onto the altar. "I would become hope." The light consumed her, and the star stopped falling. In the morning, a new constellation burned in the sky, shaped like a woman reaching for the dawn.
"}}
